  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Pradeep Bhardwaj versus Priya pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_7_534_540','2025INSC852'); ><font size='4'> <strong>PRADEEP BHARDWAJ<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>PRIYA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 534</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 852</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002902025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards the correctness of the judgment passed by the High Court dismissing the matrimonial appeal filed by the appellant-husband refusing to grant divorce to the parties. Headnotes&dagger; Hindu Marriage Act, 1955 &ndash; s.13(1)(a) &ndash; Divorce &ndash; on the ground of cruelty by the appellant-husband &ndash; Dismissed by the family court &ndash; Thereagainst, an appeal by the appellant on the ground of irretrievable breakdown of marriage and animosity between the parties &ndash; Dismissed by the High Court &ndash; Challenge to: Held: Fit<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 15-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 9502/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_7_534_540','2025INSC852','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary